      "content": "but \"deliberate effort\" takes a lifetime of being mediocre. i don't have the energy for that. and honestly, look at history. most people who \"made a mark\" weren't just kind people or nice mentors. they were people who lived these intense, tragic, or dramatic lives that people can't stop talking about. most people's lives are just... quiet. and quiet is just another word for being invisible. wouldn't it be better to be a legend for something intense rather than a ghost that nobody even realized was gone?",
